                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system southeast of the Bight will continue to move southeastwards to be centred southeast of Tasmania by Sunday allowing a trough over WA to link to a weak front south of the Bight moving over western and southern parts of SA later Sunday into Monday. Another high pressure system is expected to follow early next week.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
